1.pokedex_entries: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.
1.name: Bulbizarre

10.pokedex_entries: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.
10.name: Chenipan

100.pokedex_entries: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
100.name: Voltorbe

101.pokedex_entries: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.
101.name: Électrode

102.pokedex_entries: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
102.name: Nœunœuf

103.pokedex_entries: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
103.name: Noadkoko

104.pokedex_entries: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
104.name: Osselait

105.pokedex_entries: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.
105.name: Ossatueur

106.pokedex_entries: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.
106.name: Kicklee

107.pokedex_entries: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.
107.name: Tygnon

108.pokedex_entries: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.
108.name: Excelangue

109.pokedex_entries: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.
109.name: Smogo

11.pokedex_entries: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.
11.name: Chrysacier

110.pokedex_entries: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.
110.name: Smogogo

111.pokedex_entries: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.
111.name: Rhinocorne

112.pokedex_entries: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.
112.name: Rhinoféros

113.pokedex_entries: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.
113.name: Leveinard

114.pokedex_entries: The blue vines shrouding its body are covered in a growth of fine hair. It is known to be ticklish.
114.name: Saquedeneu

115.pokedex_entries: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.
115.name: Kangourex

116.pokedex_entries: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.
116.name: Hypotrempe

117.pokedex_entries: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.
117.name: Hypocéan

118.pokedex_entries: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.
118.name: Poissirène

119.pokedex_entries: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.
119.name: Poissoroy

12.pokedex_entries: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
12.name: Papilusion

120.pokedex_entries: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
120.name: Stari

121.pokedex_entries: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.
121.name: Staross

122.pokedex_entries: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.
122.name: M. Mime

123.pokedex_entries: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
123.name: Insécateur

124.pokedex_entries: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
124.name: Lippoutou

125.pokedex_entries: It windmills its arms to slightly boost its punches. Foes have been known to escape in the meantime.
125.name: Élektek

126.pokedex_entries: When it breathes deeply, heat waves form around its body, making it hard to see clearly.
126.name: Magmar

127.pokedex_entries: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.
127.name: Scarabrute

128.pokedex_entries: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.
128.name: Tauros

129.pokedex_entries: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.
129.name: Magicarpe

13.pokedex_entries: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.
13.name: Aspicot

130.pokedex_entries: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.
130.name: Léviator

131.pokedex_entries: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.
131.name: Lokhlass

132.pokedex_entries: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.
132.name: Métamorph

133.pokedex_entries: Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.
133.name: Évoli

134.pokedex_entries: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can melt away into water.
134.name: Aquali

135.pokedex_entries: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.
135.name: Voltali

136.pokedex_entries: Inhaled air is heated in the flame sac in its body to an intense fire over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
136.name: Pyroli

137.pokedex_entries: A man-made Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.
137.name: Porygon

138.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.
138.name: Amonita

139.pokedex_entries: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.
139.name: Amonistar

14.pokedex_entries: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
14.name: Coconfort

140.pokedex_entries: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.
140.name: Kabuto

141.pokedex_entries: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
141.name: Kabutops

142.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.
142.name: Ptéra

143.pokedex_entries: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.
143.name: Ronflex

144.pokedex_entries: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
144.name: Artikodin

145.pokedex_entries: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
145.name: Électhor

146.pokedex_entries: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.
146.name: Sulfura

147.pokedex_entries: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.
147.name: Minidraco

148.pokedex_entries: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.
148.name: Draco

149.pokedex_entries: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.
149.name: Dracolosse

15.pokedex_entries: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.
15.name: Dardargnan

150.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
150.name: Mewtwo

151.pokedex_entries: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.
151.name: Mew

152.pokedex_entries: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
152.name: Germignon

153.pokedex_entries: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
153.name: Macronium

154.pokedex_entries: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.
154.name: Méganium

155.pokedex_entries: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.
155.name: Héricendre

156.pokedex_entries: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.
156.name: Feurisson

157.pokedex_entries: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.
157.name: Typhlosion

158.pokedex_entries: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.
158.name: Kaiminus

159.pokedex_entries: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.
159.name: Crocrodil

16.pokedex_entries: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
16.name: Roucool

160.pokedex_entries: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
160.name: Aligatueur

161.pokedex_entries: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.
161.name: Fouinette

162.pokedex_entries: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
162.name: Fouinar

163.pokedex_entries: It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world's ways.
163.name: Hoothoot

164.pokedex_entries: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.
164.name: Noarfang

165.pokedex_entries: It is so timid, it can't move if it isn't with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.
165.name: Coxy

166.pokedex_entries: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.
166.name: Coxyclaque

167.pokedex_entries: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.
167.name: Mimigal

168.pokedex_entries: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
168.name: Migalos

169.pokedex_entries: The transformation of its legs into wings made it better at flying, but more clumsy at walking.
169.name: Nostenfer

17.pokedex_entries: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.
17.name: Roucoups

170.pokedex_entries: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.
170.name: Loupio

171.pokedex_entries: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed "The Deep-Sea Star."
171.name: Lanturn

172.pokedex_entries: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.
172.name: Pichu

173.pokedex_entries: It is often seen when shooting stars fill the night skies. It's said to arrive riding on a shooting star.
173.name: Mélo

174.pokedex_entries: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.
174.name: Toudoudou

175.pokedex_entries: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.
175.name: Togepi

176.pokedex_entries: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kind-hearted people.
176.name: Togetic

177.pokedex_entries: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
177.name: Natu

178.pokedex_entries: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movements all day.
178.name: Xatu

179.pokedex_entries: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.
179.name: Wattouat

18.pokedex_entries: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
18.name: Roucarnage

180.pokedex_entries: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.
180.name: Lainergie

181.pokedex_entries: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.
181.name: Pharamp

182.pokedex_entries: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
182.name: Joliflor

183.pokedex_entries: The oil-filled end of its tail floats on water. It keeps Marill from drowning even in a strong current.
183.name: Marill

184.pokedex_entries: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.
184.name: Azumarill

185.pokedex_entries: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.
185.name: Simularbre

186.pokedex_entries: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.
186.name: Tarpaud

187.pokedex_entries: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.
187.name: Granivol

188.pokedex_entries: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.
188.name: Floravol

189.pokedex_entries: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.
189.name: Cotovol

19.pokedex_entries: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
19.name: Rattata

190.pokedex_entries: It lives high among the treetops. It can use its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.
190.name: Capumain

191.pokedex_entries: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.
191.name: Tournegrin

192.pokedex_entries: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.
192.name: Héliatronc

193.pokedex_entries: It can hover in one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.
193.name: Yanma

194.pokedex_entries: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.
194.name: Axoloto

195.pokedex_entries: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and rocks while swimming.
195.name: Maraiste

196.pokedex_entries: Its fur is so sensitive, it can sense minute shifts in the air and predict the weather.
196.name: Mentali

197.pokedex_entries: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.
197.name: Noctali

198.pokedex_entries: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.
198.name: Cornèbre

199.pokedex_entries: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.
199.name: Roigada

2.pokedex_entries: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.
2.name: Herbizarre

20.pokedex_entries: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.
20.name: Rattatac

200.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.
200.name: Feuforêve

201.pokedex_entries: When alone, nothing happens. However, if there are two or more, an odd power is said to emerge.
201.name: Zarbi

202.pokedex_entries: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.
202.name: Qulbutoké

203.pokedex_entries: The head on its tail contains a small brain. It can instinctively fight even while facing backward.
203.name: Girafarig

204.pokedex_entries: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.
204.name: Pomdepic

205.pokedex_entries: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.
205.name: Foretress

206.pokedex_entries: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.
206.name: Insolourdo

207.pokedex_entries: It glides as if sliding. It startles foes by clamping on their faces, then jabs with its poison stinger.
207.name: Scorplane

208.pokedex_entries: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
208.name: Steelix

209.pokedex_entries: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.
209.name: Snubbull

21.pokedex_entries: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
21.name: Piafabec

210.pokedex_entries: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.
210.name: Granbull

211.pokedex_entries: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.
211.name: Qwilfish

212.pokedex_entries: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.
212.name: Cizayox

213.pokedex_entries: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.
213.name: Caratroc

214.pokedex_entries: It loves sweet honey. To keep all the honey to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.
214.name: Scarhino

215.pokedex_entries: A smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal Eggs by having one lure the parents away.
215.name: Farfuret

216.pokedex_entries: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.
216.name: Teddiursa

217.pokedex_entries: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.
217.name: Ursaring

218.pokedex_entries: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
218.name: Limagma

219.pokedex_entries: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.
219.name: Volcaropod

22.pokedex_entries: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights using its sharp beak.
22.name: Rapasdepic

220.pokedex_entries: It has a very sensitive nose. It can locate mushrooms, berries, and even hot springs buried under ice.
220.name: Marcacrin

221.pokedex_entries: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is strong against the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.
221.name: Cochignon

222.pokedex_entries: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.
222.name: Corayon

223.pokedex_entries: It forcefully squirts water. The water jet never misses prey even if the Remoraid is deep in the sea.
223.name: Rémoraid

224.pokedex_entries: It loves to lurk inside holes in rocks. It sometimes sprays ink on prey by sticking out only its mouth.
224.name: Octillery

225.pokedex_entries: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.
225.name: Cadoizo

226.pokedex_entries: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.
226.name: Démanta

227.pokedex_entries: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speed of over 180 mph.
227.name: Airmure

228.pokedex_entries: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.
228.name: Malosse

229.pokedex_entries: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
229.name: Démolosse

23.pokedex_entries: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.
23.name: Abo

230.pokedex_entries: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.
230.name: Hyporoi

231.pokedex_entries: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
231.name: Phanpy

232.pokedex_entries: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.
232.name: Donphan

233.pokedex_entries: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.
233.name: Porygon2

234.pokedex_entries: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.
234.name: Cerfrousse

235.pokedex_entries: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.
235.name: Queulorior

236.pokedex_entries: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.
236.name: Debugant

237.pokedex_entries: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.
237.name: Kapoera

238.pokedex_entries: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
238.name: Lippouti

239.pokedex_entries: A weak electric current flows between its horns. Sticking a hand there shocks the unwary.
239.name: Élekid

24.pokedex_entries: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes when they are frozen in fear.
24.name: Arbok

240.pokedex_entries: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body's heat can top 1,100 degrees F.
240.name: Magby

241.pokedex_entries: It is said that kids who drink Miltank's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.
241.name: Écrémeuh

242.pokedex_entries: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
242.name: Leuphorie

243.pokedex_entries: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.
243.name: Raikou

244.pokedex_entries: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
244.name: Entei

245.pokedex_entries: It travels across the world to purify polluted water. It moves together with the north wind.
245.name: Suicune

246.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.
246.name: Embrylex

247.pokedex_entries: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.
247.name: Ymphect

248.pokedex_entries: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
248.name: Tyranocif

249.pokedex_entries: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.
249.name: Lugia

25.pokedex_entries: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
25.name: Pikachu

250.pokedex_entries: It possesses seven-colored wings. It is said that those who see Ho-Oh are promised an eternal happiness.
250.name: Ho-Oh

251.pokedex_entries: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.
251.name: Celebi

252.pokedex_entries: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.
252.name: Arcko

253.pokedex_entries: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.
253.name: Massko

254.pokedex_entries: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.
254.name: Jungko

255.pokedex_entries: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.
255.name: Poussifeu

256.pokedex_entries: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.
256.name: Galifeu

257.pokedex_entries: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.
257.name: Braségali

258.pokedex_entries: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to lift boulders.
258.name: Gobou

259.pokedex_entries: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.
259.name: Flobio

26.pokedex_entries: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
26.name: Raichu

260.pokedex_entries: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
260.name: Laggron

261.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
261.name: Medhyèna

262.pokedex_entries: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.
262.name: Grahyèna

263.pokedex_entries: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
263.name: Zigzaton

264.pokedex_entries: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
264.name: Linéon

265.pokedex_entries: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.
265.name: Chenipotte

266.pokedex_entries: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.
266.name: Armulys

267.pokedex_entries: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.
267.name: Charmillon

268.pokedex_entries: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.
268.name: Blindalys

269.pokedex_entries: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.
269.name: Papinox

27.pokedex_entries: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
27.name: Sabelette

270.pokedex_entries: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can't swim.
270.name: Nénupiot

271.pokedex_entries: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
271.name: Lombre

272.pokedex_entries: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.
272.name: Ludicolo

273.pokedex_entries: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.
273.name: Grainipiot

274.pokedex_entries: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.
274.name: Pifeuil

275.pokedex_entries: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.
275.name: Tengalice

276.pokedex_entries: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
276.name: Nirondelle

277.pokedex_entries: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.
277.name: Hélédelle

278.pokedex_entries: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.
278.name: Goélise

279.pokedex_entries: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.
279.name: Bekipan

28.pokedex_entries: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.
28.name: Sablaireau

280.pokedex_entries: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
280.name: Tarsal

281.pokedex_entries: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
281.name: Kirlia

282.pokedex_entries: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
282.name: Gardevoir

283.pokedex_entries: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.
283.name: Arakdo

284.pokedex_entries: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.
284.name: Maskadra

285.pokedex_entries: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.
285.name: Balignon

286.pokedex_entries: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.
286.name: Chapignon

287.pokedex_entries: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.
287.name: Parecool

288.pokedex_entries: Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still even for a moment.
288.name: Vigoroth

289.pokedex_entries: The world's laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.
289.name: Monaflèmit

29.pokedex_entries: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from its barbs can be fatal.
29.name: Nidoran♀

290.pokedex_entries: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.
290.name: Ningale

291.pokedex_entries: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.
291.name: Ninjask

292.pokedex_entries: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.
292.name: Munja

293.pokedex_entries: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.
293.name: Chuchmur

294.pokedex_entries: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
294.name: Ramboum

295.pokedex_entries: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
295.name: Brouhabam

296.pokedex_entries: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.
296.name: Makuhita

297.pokedex_entries: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.
297.name: Hariyama

298.pokedex_entries: Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.
298.name: Azurill

299.pokedex_entries: When endangered, it may protect itself by raising its magnetism and drawing iron objects to its body.
299.name: Tarinor

3.pokedex_entries: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.
3.name: Florizarre

30.pokedex_entries: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorino's.
30.name: Nidorina

300.pokedex_entries: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.
300.name: Skitty

301.pokedex_entries: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
301.name: Delcatty

302.pokedex_entries: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.
302.name: Ténéfix

303.pokedex_entries: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
303.name: Mysdibule

304.pokedex_entries: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.
304.name: Galekid

305.pokedex_entries: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.
305.name: Galegon

306.pokedex_entries: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
306.name: Galeking

307.pokedex_entries: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.
307.name: Méditikka

308.pokedex_entries: It gains the ability to see the aura of its opponents by honing its mind through starvation.
308.name: Charmina

309.pokedex_entries: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
309.name: Dynavolt

31.pokedex_entries: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.
31.name: Nidoqueen

310.pokedex_entries: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
310.name: Élecsprint

311.pokedex_entries: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
311.name: Posipi

312.pokedex_entries: It cheers on its friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
312.name: Négapi

313.pokedex_entries: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise's sweet aroma.
313.name: Muciole

314.pokedex_entries: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.
314.name: Lumivole

315.pokedex_entries: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers' aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.
315.name: Rosélia

316.pokedex_entries: Almost all of its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.
316.name: Gloupti

317.pokedex_entries: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.
317.name: Avaltout

318.pokedex_entries: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.
318.name: Carvanha

319.pokedex_entries: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."
319.name: Sharpedo

32.pokedex_entries: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
32.name: Nidoran♂

320.pokedex_entries: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.
320.name: Wailmer

321.pokedex_entries: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
321.name: Wailord

322.pokedex_entries: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.
322.name: Chamallot

323.pokedex_entries: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.
323.name: Camérupt

324.pokedex_entries: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.
324.name: Chartor

325.pokedex_entries: It bounces constantly, using its tail as a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.
325.name: Spoink

326.pokedex_entries: It uses black pearls to amplify its psycho-power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.
326.name: Groret

327.pokedex_entries: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
327.name: Spinda

328.pokedex_entries: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
328.name: Kraknoix

329.pokedex_entries: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.
329.name: Vibraninf

33.pokedex_entries: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.
33.name: Nidorino

330.pokedex_entries: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as "The Desert Spirit."
330.name: Libégon

331.pokedex_entries: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.
331.name: Cacnea

332.pokedex_entries: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day's desert heat.
332.name: Cacturne

333.pokedex_entries: It can't relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.
333.name: Tylton

334.pokedex_entries: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.
334.name: Altaria

335.pokedex_entries: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.
335.name: Mangriff

336.pokedex_entries: For many generations, it has feuded with Zangoose. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.
336.name: Séviper

337.pokedex_entries: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.
337.name: Séléroc

338.pokedex_entries: A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.
338.name: Solaroc

339.pokedex_entries: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.
339.name: Barloche

34.pokedex_entries: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
34.name: Nidoking

340.pokedex_entries: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.
340.name: Barbicha

341.pokedex_entries: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
341.name: Écrapince

342.pokedex_entries: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.
342.name: Colhomard

343.pokedex_entries: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
343.name: Balbuto

344.pokedex_entries: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.
344.name: Kaorine

345.pokedex_entries: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
345.name: Lilia

346.pokedex_entries: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up its prey from the beaches.
346.name: Vacilys

347.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.
347.name: Anorith

348.pokedex_entries: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.
348.name: Armaldo

349.pokedex_entries: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.
349.name: Barpau

35.pokedex_entries: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.
35.name: Mélofée

350.pokedex_entries: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.
350.name: Milobellus

351.pokedex_entries: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.
351.name: Morphéo

352.pokedex_entries: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.
352.name: Kecleon

353.pokedex_entries: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
353.name: Polichombr

354.pokedex_entries: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.
354.name: Branette

355.pokedex_entries: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.
355.name: Skelénox

356.pokedex_entries: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.
356.name: Téraclope

357.pokedex_entries: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.
357.name: Tropius

358.pokedex_entries: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.
358.name: Éoko

359.pokedex_entries: Rumored to sense danger with its horn, it became a target. It fled deep into the mountains.
359.name: Absol

36.pokedex_entries: It is very wary and rarely shows itself to people. Its ears can hear a pin drop over half a mile away.
36.name: Mélodelfe

360.pokedex_entries: It grows stronger by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.
360.name: Okéoké

361.pokedex_entries: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
361.name: Stalgamin

362.pokedex_entries: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.
362.name: Oniglali

363.pokedex_entries: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.
363.name: Obalie

364.pokedex_entries: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.
364.name: Phogleur

365.pokedex_entries: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.
365.name: Kaimorse

366.pokedex_entries: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.
366.name: Coquiperl

367.pokedex_entries: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.
367.name: Serpang

368.pokedex_entries: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.
368.name: Rosabyss

369.pokedex_entries: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
369.name: Relicanth

37.pokedex_entries: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.
37.name: Goupix

370.pokedex_entries: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.
370.name: Lovdisc

371.pokedex_entries: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.
371.name: Draby

372.pokedex_entries: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.
372.name: Drackhaus

373.pokedex_entries: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.
373.name: Drattak

374.pokedex_entries: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
374.name: Terhal

375.pokedex_entries: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.
375.name: Métang

376.pokedex_entries: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
376.name: Métalosse

377.pokedex_entries: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.
377.name: Regirock

378.pokedex_entries: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
378.name: Regice

379.pokedex_entries: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.
379.name: Registeel

38.pokedex_entries: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.
38.name: Feunard

380.pokedex_entries: Its body is covered in a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
380.name: Latias

381.pokedex_entries: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
381.name: Latios

382.pokedex_entries: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
382.name: Kyogre

383.pokedex_entries: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
383.name: Groudon

384.pokedex_entries: It cannot be seen from ground level since it lives far up above the clouds in the ozone layer.
384.name: Rayquaza

385.pokedex_entries: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
385.name: Jirachi

386.pokedex_entries: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.
386.name: Deoxys

387.pokedex_entries: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.
387.name: Tortipouss

388.pokedex_entries: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.
388.name: Boskara

389.pokedex_entries: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there.
389.name: Torterra

39.pokedex_entries: When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.
39.name: Rondoudou

390.pokedex_entries: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.
390.name: Ouisticram

391.pokedex_entries: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.
391.name: Chimpenfeu

392.pokedex_entries: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.
392.name: Simiabraz

393.pokedex_entries: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.
393.name: Tiplouf

394.pokedex_entries: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.
394.name: Prinplouf

395.pokedex_entries: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.
395.name: Pingoléon

396.pokedex_entries: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
396.name: Étourmi

397.pokedex_entries: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.
397.name: Étourvol

398.pokedex_entries: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
398.name: Étouraptor

399.pokedex_entries: A comparison revealed that Bidoof's front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's.
399.name: Keunottor

4.pokedex_entries: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.
4.name: Salamèche

40.pokedex_entries: Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.
40.name: Grodoudou

400.pokedex_entries: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.
400.name: Castorno

401.pokedex_entries: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.
401.name: Crikzik

402.pokedex_entries: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.
402.name: Mélokrik

403.pokedex_entries: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
403.name: Lixy

404.pokedex_entries: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
404.name: Luxio

405.pokedex_entries: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.
405.name: Luxray

406.pokedex_entries: Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun's warm touch.
406.name: Rozbouton

407.pokedex_entries: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.
407.name: Roserade

408.pokedex_entries: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.
408.name: Kranidos

409.pokedex_entries: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.
409.name: Charkos

41.pokedex_entries: It checks its surroundings and location using reflections of the ultrasonic waves from its mouth.
41.name: Nosferapti

410.pokedex_entries: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.
410.name: Dinoclier

411.pokedex_entries: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.
411.name: Bastiodon

412.pokedex_entries: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.
412.name: Cheniti

413.pokedex_entries: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.
413.name: Cheniselle

414.pokedex_entries: While it loves floral honey, it won't gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from Combee.
414.name: Papilord

415.pokedex_entries: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.
415.name: Apitrini

416.pokedex_entries: It releases various pheromones to make the grubs in its body do its bidding while fighting foes.
416.name: Apireine

417.pokedex_entries: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
417.name: Pachirisu

418.pokedex_entries: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.
418.name: Mustébouée

419.pokedex_entries: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.
419.name: Mustéflott

42.pokedex_entries: Its sharp fangs puncture the toughest of hides and have small holes for greedily sucking blood.
42.name: Nosferalto

420.pokedex_entries: The small ball is not only full of nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.
420.name: Ceribou

421.pokedex_entries: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.
421.name: Ceriflor

422.pokedex_entries: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.
422.name: Sancoki

423.pokedex_entries: Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.
423.name: Tritosor

424.pokedex_entries: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.
424.name: Capidextre

425.pokedex_entries: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."
425.name: Baudrive

426.pokedex_entries: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.
426.name: Grodrive

427.pokedex_entries: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.
427.name: Laporeille

428.pokedex_entries: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.
428.name: Lockpin

429.pokedex_entries: Its cry sounds like incantation. It is said that the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.
429.name: Magirêve

43.pokedex_entries: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.
43.name: Mystherbe

430.pokedex_entries: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."
430.name: Corboss

431.pokedex_entries: It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn't fed.
431.name: Chaglam

432.pokedex_entries: It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.
432.name: Chaffreux

433.pokedex_entries: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.
433.name: Korillon

434.pokedex_entries: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.
434.name: Moufouette

435.pokedex_entries: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.
435.name: Moufflair

436.pokedex_entries: There are researchers who believe this Pokémon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.
436.name: Archéomire

437.pokedex_entries: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.
437.name: Archéodong

438.pokedex_entries: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.
438.name: Manzaï

439.pokedex_entries: It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.
439.name: Mime Jr

44.pokedex_entries: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.
44.name: Ortide

440.pokedex_entries: It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others' feet and cause them to stumble.
440.name: Ptiravi

441.pokedex_entries: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.
441.name: Pijako

442.pokedex_entries: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.
442.name: Spiritomb

443.pokedex_entries: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.
443.name: Griknot

444.pokedex_entries: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot into its nest.
444.name: Carmache

445.pokedex_entries: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
445.name: Carchacrok

446.pokedex_entries: In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.
446.name: Goinfrex

447.pokedex_entries: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.
447.name: Riolu

448.pokedex_entries: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
448.name: Lucario

449.pokedex_entries: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through the sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.
449.name: Hippopotas

45.pokedex_entries: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
45.name: Rafflésia

450.pokedex_entries: Surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of strength.
450.name: Hippodocus

451.pokedex_entries: As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.
451.name: Rapion

452.pokedex_entries: Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.
452.name: Drascore

453.pokedex_entries: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
453.name: Cradopaud

454.pokedex_entries: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for more potency.
454.name: Coatox

455.pokedex_entries: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
455.name: Vortente

456.pokedex_entries: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.
456.name: Écayon

457.pokedex_entries: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with Lanturn.
457.name: Luminéon

458.pokedex_entries: People organize tours to see this Pokémon frolic and skim the tops of the waves with Remoraid.
458.name: Babimanta

459.pokedex_entries: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
459.name: Blizzi

46.pokedex_entries: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.
46.name: Paras

460.pokedex_entries: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
460.name: Blizzaroi

461.pokedex_entries: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.
461.name: Dimoret

462.pokedex_entries: A group tried to use scientific means to make Magnezone evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.
462.name: Magnézone

463.pokedex_entries: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.
463.name: Coudlangue

464.pokedex_entries: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding its muscles instantly.
464.name: Rhinastoc

465.pokedex_entries: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.
465.name: Bouldeneu

466.pokedex_entries: Heedless of enemy attacks, it closes in, shoves its tails onto the foe, then looses high voltage.
466.name: Élekable

467.pokedex_entries: When launching 3,600 degrees F fireballs, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.
467.name: Maganon

468.pokedex_entries: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.
468.name: Togekiss

469.pokedex_entries: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.
469.name: Yanméga

47.pokedex_entries: A mushroom grown larger than the host's body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.
47.name: Parasect

470.pokedex_entries: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.
470.name: Phyllali

471.pokedex_entries: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.
471.name: Givrali

472.pokedex_entries: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.
472.name: Scorvol

473.pokedex_entries: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.
473.name: Mammochon

474.pokedex_entries: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.
474.name: Porygon-Z

475.pokedex_entries: When protecting someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.
475.name: Gallame

476.pokedex_entries: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
476.name: Tarinorme

477.pokedex_entries: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
477.name: Noctunoir

478.pokedex_entries: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degree F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
478.name: Momartik

479.pokedex_entries: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.
479.name: Motisma

48.pokedex_entries: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.
48.name: Mimitoss

480.pokedex_entries: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.
480.name: Créhelf

481.pokedex_entries: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.
481.name: Créfollet

482.pokedex_entries: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.
482.name: Créfadet

483.pokedex_entries: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga's heart beats.
483.name: Dialga

484.pokedex_entries: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia's every breath.
484.name: Palkia

485.pokedex_entries: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.
485.name: Heatran

486.pokedex_entries: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
486.name: Regigigas

487.pokedex_entries: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
487.name: Giratina

488.pokedex_entries: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.
488.name: Cresselia

489.pokedex_entries: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
489.name: Phione

49.pokedex_entries: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.
49.name: Aéromite

490.pokedex_entries: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.
490.name: Manaphy

491.pokedex_entries: To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.
491.name: Darkrai

492.pokedex_entries: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.
492.name: Shaymin

493.pokedex_entries: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.
493.name: Arceus

5.pokedex_entries: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
5.name: Reptincel

50.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.
50.name: Taupiqueur

51.pokedex_entries: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.
51.name: Triopikeur

52.pokedex_entries: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.
52.name: Miaouss

53.pokedex_entries: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.
53.name: Persian

54.pokedex_entries: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
54.name: Psykokwak

55.pokedex_entries: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.
55.name: Akwakwak

56.pokedex_entries: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.
56.name: Férosinge

57.pokedex_entries: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.
57.name: Colossinge

58.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.
58.name: Caninos

59.pokedex_entries: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.
59.name: Arcanin

6.pokedex_entries: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
6.name: Dracaufeu

60.pokedex_entries: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.
60.name: Ptitard

61.pokedex_entries: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.
61.name: Têtarte

62.pokedex_entries: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.
62.name: Tartard

63.pokedex_entries: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.
63.name: Abra

64.pokedex_entries: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.
64.name: Kadabra

65.pokedex_entries: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
65.name: Alakazam

66.pokedex_entries: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
66.name: Machoc

67.pokedex_entries: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.
67.name: Machopeur

68.pokedex_entries: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.
68.name: Mackogneur

69.pokedex_entries: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.
69.name: Chétiflor

7.pokedex_entries: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
7.name: Carapuce

70.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.
70.name: Boustiflor

71.pokedex_entries: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.
71.name: Empiflor

72.pokedex_entries: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.
72.name: Tentacool

73.pokedex_entries: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
73.name: Tentacruel

74.pokedex_entries: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.
74.name: Racaillou

75.pokedex_entries: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.
75.name: Gravalanch

76.pokedex_entries: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.
76.name: Grolem

77.pokedex_entries: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.
77.name: Ponyta

78.pokedex_entries: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.
78.name: Galopa

79.pokedex_entries: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.
79.name: Ramoloss

8.pokedex_entries: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
8.name: Carabaffe

80.pokedex_entries: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
80.name: Flagadoss

81.pokedex_entries: The faster the units at its sides rotate, the greater the magnetic force they generate.
81.name: Magnéti

82.pokedex_entries: Many mysteriously appear when more sunspots dot the sun. They stop TV sets from displaying properly.
82.name: Magnéton

83.pokedex_entries: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
83.name: Canarticho

84.pokedex_entries: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with telepathic power.
84.name: Doduo

85.pokedex_entries: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.
85.name: Dodrio

86.pokedex_entries: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.
86.name: Otaria

87.pokedex_entries: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
87.name: Lamantine

88.pokedex_entries: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.
88.name: Tadmorv

89.pokedex_entries: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.
89.name: Grotadmorv

9.pokedex_entries: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
9.name: Tortank

90.pokedex_entries: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.
90.name: Kokiyas

91.pokedex_entries: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.
91.name: Crustabri

92.pokedex_entries: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.
92.name: Fantominus

93.pokedex_entries: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
93.name: Spectrum

94.pokedex_entries: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.
94.name: Ectoplasma

95.pokedex_entries: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
95.name: Onix

96.pokedex_entries: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
96.name: Soporifik

97.pokedex_entries: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.
97.name: Hypnomade

98.pokedex_entries: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.
98.name: Krabby

99.pokedex_entries: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.
99.name: Krabboss
